"{\"uid\": \"inews.co.uk-sport-team-gb-paris-olympics-athletes-full-list-3184574\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"IMPARTIAL NEWS + INTELLIGENT DEBATE  Account  327 athletes are taking part in the Paris Olympics 2024 for Team GB including 33 former Olympic champions  Team GB's athletes are primed and ready to compete in theParis Olympics 2024.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 230, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 153, \"end\": 160, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8055920643111606e-23, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thousands of sportsmen and women have descended on the French capitalin readiness for the event, which officiallygets under way on Friday 26 July.\", \"from\": 232, \"to\": 378, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 287, \"end\": 293, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9772404420248396, \"rank\": 0.019962808068156215, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thomas Bach, the International Olympic Committee President, said: \\\"You can also feel, see, hear the excitement growing, not only in Paris but all of France.\", \"from\": 380, \"to\": 536, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 380, \"end\": 391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\"}, {\"begin\": 397, \"end\": 428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 512, \"end\": 517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 3.4824510203455817e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 529, \"end\": 535, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9363340242060953, \"rank\": 0.03866069610493077, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"More than six million people lined the streets of France to watch the Olympic flame.\", \"from\": 538, \"to\": 623, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 589, \"end\": 595, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9363340242060953, \"rank\": 0.03866069610493077, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"What commitment\\u2026 Everybody is excited about the Games and longing for the moment it finally starts.\\\"\", \"from\": 625, \"to\": 726, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Great Britain has 327 athletes competing across 24 sports, with the youngest 16-year-old skateboarder Sky Brown and the oldest 57-year-old Carl Hester in dressage.\", \"from\": 728, \"to\": 891, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 728, \"end\": 741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999545253, \"rank\": 4.543911831726257e-11, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 830, \"end\": 839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Brown\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sky Brown\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Brown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Brown\"}, {\"begin\": 867, \"end\": 878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Hester\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carl Hester\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Hester\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Hester\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The team comprises 169 veterans of the Olympic Games and 74 former medallists including 33 Olympic champions.\", \"from\": 893, \"to\": 1002, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Remarkably, there are also 18 athletes who competed at London 2012 who will be returning to the Games 12 years later.\", \"from\": 1004, \"to\": 1121, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1059, \"end\": 1070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999998267413, \"rank\": 1.732764228655187e-10, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We take a look at who will be taking part on behalf of Team GB.\", \"from\": 1123, \"to\": 1186, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1178, \"end\": 1185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8055920643111606e-23, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Women's team:  Men's team:  Men's Marathon:  Women's Marathon:  Women's team:  Men's team:  Women's team:  Men's team:  Marathon swimming:  UK Sport, the high performance sport agency, is hoping Team GB will bring back between50 and 70 medals this year from Paris.\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1452, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1328, \"end\": 1336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UK Sport\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\"}, {\"begin\": 1383, \"end\": 1390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8055920643111606e-23, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 1446, \"end\": 1451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 3.4824510203455817e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Previously, Team GB has won 51 (Beijing 2008), 65 (London 2012), 67 (Rio 2016) and 64 (Tokyo 2020) medals, finishing fourth in the Tokyo 2020 medal table with 22 gold, 20 silver and 22 bronze medals.\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1653, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1466, \"end\": 1473, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8055920643111606e-23, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 1585, \"end\": 1590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999862785684924, \"rank\": 1.3721619880632235e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dr Kate Baker, UK Sport Director of Performance said: \\\"GB currently boasts 41 current world champions in Olympic disciplines and a further 61 in Paralympic disciplines, highlighting the immense talent across our sports.\", \"from\": 1655, \"to\": 1874, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1658, \"end\": 1668, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Baker\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kate Baker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Baker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Baker\"}, {\"begin\": 1670, \"end\": 1678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UK Sport\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\"}, {\"begin\": 1710, \"end\": 1712, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.999999922461487, \"rank\": 7.75387144479015e-08, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We want to continue our streak of top five Olympic medal table finishes, but that will not be easy.\\\"\", \"from\": 1876, \"to\": 1977, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"GB medal hopes are being pinned on runner Keely Hodgkinson who has odds of 2/5 with bookmakers William Hill to win gold in the 800m event.\", \"from\": 1979, \"to\": 2117, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2021, \"end\": 2037, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keely Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\"}, {\"begin\": 2074, \"end\": 2086, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Hill_(bookmaker)\", \"score\": 0.941682356775323